[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | 
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \hypertarget{implementation-and-theory}{%
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \section{Implementation and theory}\label{implementation-and-theory}}
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | 
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \hypertarget{filter-banks-spafefbanks}{%
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \subsection{\texorpdfstring{Filter banks
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | (\texttt{spafe/fbanks})}{Filter banks (spafe/fbanks)}}\label{filter-banks-spafefbanks}}
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | 
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | A filter bank is defined as an array of band pass filters that splits
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | the input signal into a set of analysis signals, each one carrying a
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | single frequency sub-band of the original signal
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | (\protect\hyperlink{ref-penedo:2019}{Penedo et al., 2019};
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \protect\hyperlink{ref-sarangi:2020}{Sarangi et al., 2020}). Each band
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | pass filter is centered at a different frequency, called center
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | frequency. The center frequencies are evenly spaced over a specificied
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | scaled frequencies range(e.g.~bark scale, erb scale, mel scale etc.).
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | The bandwidths of the filters increase with the frequency, in order to
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | duplicate the human hearing properties, which are characterized by a
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | decreasing sensitivity at higher frequencies. Within this context, spafe
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | provides implementations for the following filter banks: \textbf{Bark
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | filter banks}, \textbf{Gammatone filter banks}, \textbf{Linear filter
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | banks} and the \textbf{Mel filter banks}.
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | 
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \begin{figure}[!h]
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \begin{center}
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   |       \includegraphics[width=13.5cm]{figures/bark_fbanks.png}  
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \end{center}
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \caption{Bark filter banks computed and visualized using spafe}
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \end{figure}
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | 
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \hypertarget{features-spafefeatures}{%
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \subsection{\texorpdfstring{Features
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | (\texttt{spafe/features})}{Features (spafe/features)}}\label{features-spafefeatures}}
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | 
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | In an attempt to cover most audio features, spafe provides various
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | frequency and cepstral domain features extraction algorithms, both
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | filter bank-based and auto-regression-based. The following is a list of
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | the available features extraction routines in the spafe python package:
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | 
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \begin{table}[!h]
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \begin{center}
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   |     \begin{tabular}{l*{6}{l}llllllllllllr}
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   |          - Bark Frequency Cepstral Coefﬁcients                 & BFCC  \\
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   |          - Constant Q-transform Cepstral Coeﬃcients           & CQCC  \\
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   |          - Gammatone Frequency Cepstral Coefﬁcients            & GFCC  \\
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   |          - Linear Frequency Cepstral Coefﬁcients               & LFCC  \\
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   |          - Linear Prediction Cepstral Coeﬃcients              & LPCC  \\
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   |          - Mel Frequency Cepstral Coefﬁcients                  & MFCC  \\
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   |          - Inverse Mel Frequency Cepstral Coefﬁcients          & IMFCC \\
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   |          - Magnitude based Spectral Root Cepstral Coefficients & MSRCC \\
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   |          - Normalized Gammachirp Cepstral Coefficients         & NGCC  \\
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   |          - Power-Normalized Cepstral Coefficients              & PNCC  \\
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   |          - Phase based Spectral Root Cepstral Coefficients     & PSRCC \\
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   |          - Perceptual Linear Prediction Coefficents            & PLP   \\
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   |          - Rasta Perceptual Linear Prediction Coefficents      & RPLP  \\
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   |     \end{tabular}
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \end{center}
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \end{table}
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | 
