[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \hypertarget{frequencies-spafefrequencies}{%
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \subsection{\texorpdfstring{Frequencies
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | (\texttt{spafe/frequencies})}{Frequencies (spafe/frequencies)}}\label{frequencies-spafefrequencies}}
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | 
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | The frequencies modules in spafe focus specifically on the computation
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | of dominant and fundamental frequencies. A dominant frequency is per
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | definition the frequency carrying the maximum energy among all
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | frequencies of the spectrum
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | (\protect\hyperlink{ref-rastislav:2013}{Telgarsky, 2013}), whereas the
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | fundamental frequency (often noted as \(F_0\) ) is defined as the
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | inverse of the period of a periodic signal
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | (\protect\hyperlink{ref-cheveigne:2002}{Cheveigné \& Kawahara, 2002}).
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | 
