[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \hypertarget{utils-spafeutils}{%
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \subsection{\texorpdfstring{Utils
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | (\texttt{spafe/utils})}{Utils (spafe/utils)}}\label{utils-spafeutils}}
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | 
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | The utils scripts, handle most of the input signal pre-processing steps
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | including pre-emphasis, framing and windowing. They also include all the
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | conversion computations needed to convert Hertz frequencies to other
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | frequency scales. On top of that, all feature post-processing routines
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | are in this group. This includes normalization, liftering, deltas
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | computation and visualization.
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | 
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \hypertarget{conclusion}{%
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | \section{Conclusion}\label{conclusion}}
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | 
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | This paper introduced spafe, a python package for audio feature
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | extractions. Spafe provides a unified solution for audio features
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | extraction, that can help simplify and accelerate the research of
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | various audio-based recognition experiments.
[4e060040-933f-4471-9c12-1d55c97103b9/Paper Draft]   | 
